<br>
In Michigan, a man has just been charged with involuntary manslaughter 9 years after the fact, when the person he struck in a fight recently died while in a coma. <br>
<br>
9 years ago, the two combatants were involved in an agreed upon fight after school. One man struck the other, who in turn fell to the ground and upon impact with the concrete severed his brain stem sending him in to a coma. The first man was not charged at the time for any crime, not assault or manslaughter. However, he is now a wanted man in the state of Michigan. Unsure of what the statute of limitations is for this type of crime, but 9 years is a long time.<br>
<br>
So what is all your takes on this? <br>
<br>
Personally, I am not sure either way how it should be handled. He did cause the guy to go in to a coma that in the end caused him to die. However, it could be argued that it was self defense, and that he could have been in the same situation. Another way some are saying it could be argued is that while in the hospital he could have received bad care which caused him to die.<br>
<br>
At any rate, it's a rather screwy story to say the least. <br>
<br>
Edit: Forgot to add, at the time of the incident, both were juveniles. The one who was being charged is now 26 and is being charged as an adult. He could receive 15 years in prison for it, where as if he were charged as a juvenile,it could be like 18 months in a low security home. <p><a href=http://www.hneguild.com/profile.asp?name=Garbhad><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~cblack87/Garbsig.jpeg"></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=garbhad>Garbhad</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0> at: 2/18/03 8:12:32 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ryjalcliffwalker>Ryjal Cliffwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(2/18/03 8:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3129.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Something to ponder.</span><hr size=1> Well for one thing, a fight is a fight.<br>
Either and or both could be charged with harassment, Assault, Menacing,  Disorderly Conduct and so on.  <br>
<br>
There is no statute of limitations on a crime where a death results, be it by accident on premeditated.  The statute on most non violent crimes ( like bank robery ) is 7 years.<br>
<br>
